# Build verification

After finishing a task that changes source, headers, or CMake files, run the project build before marking the work done.

## When to run

Run `.\build.ps1` from the repo root when you:

- Added, edited, or removed `.cpp`, `.h`, or `CMakeLists.txt`
- Fixed a bug or implemented a feature in wrec source

Skip the build when you:

- Only changed docs, comments, or `.cursor/rules/`
- Only answered a question with no code edits
- The user explicitly asked not to build

## How to run

```powershell
.\build.ps1
```

Use the Shell tool with `working_directory` set to the project root (`F:/Project/cpp/wrec` or `$PSScriptRoot` equivalent).

Default is Ninja + Release (matches CI). Use `.\build.ps1 -Clean` only when configure/cache issues are suspected.

## On failure

- Read compiler/linker errors from the output
- Fix the root cause in source, not symptoms at one call site
- Re-run `.\build.ps1` until it succeeds or you hit an environment blocker (missing VS, cmake, ninja) — report blockers clearly to the user

## Done criteria

A coding task is not complete until `build.ps1` exits 0, or you documented why a build could not run in this environment.
